nodes.bodyText:
Well, actually it might be okay. The ApplicationEventsays:
/**
 * Create a new {@code ApplicationEvent}.
 * @param source the object on which the event initially occurred or with
 * which the event is associated (never {@code null})
*/
public ApplicationEvent(Object source) {
	super(source);
	this.timestamp = System.currentTimeMillis();
}

So the LandscapeDescription is the object with which the event is associated with. In other words, there has been a change on the LandscapeDescription, so that is the event.
Sounds right to me.

